e-commerce, technology being used to facilitate buying and selling. It is very normal to find a child of below 15-years-old who knows all the websites on how to buy things online and buy things online.

Getting a smartphone does not signify that the owner is aware about this thing called e-commerce. It is very addictive and dangerous. Like any other things, it needs moderation.

Very sensitive to speed

Quite recently I was wondering who invented the extra button pronounced '”;s” which is found on various websites.

On this button real people's income is handled, on this button fake people's income is handled, on this button you can access various things online which maybe not be appropriate for you. Parents should be considerate of this when they handover smartphones to their kids.

If this speed is seen on the adult the problem can be Mechanical.

Free education

Many governmental and private institutions offer free education to the youth. By now in the 21st century, all the people who are supposed to study have been studying for quite sometime. The digital divide has blurred lines. Those who are supposed to be outside the digital world are using smartphones like there is no tomorrow.

These smartphones bring the world to them, and as it is in the Thirties, Forty and Fifty people would rather stay indoors than come near technology. One thing good about this reluctance is that they get focus with their studies. One thing should follow in a classroom, quality results.
